Beware of Fake Paneer in India❗️

Many markets are selling adulterated paneer made from starch, synthetic milk, and harmful chemicals. Consuming fake paneer can cause food poisoning, digestive issues, and long-term health risks. 

✅ How to Identify Real Paneer?

👉🏼Smell Test: Real paneer has a fresh, milky aroma, while fake paneer may smell sour or chemical-like. 
👉🏼Texture Test: Genuine paneer is soft and crumbles slightly, whereas fake paneer feels rubbery. 
👉🏼Hot Water Test: Drop a piece in hot water—if it dissolves or turns slimy, it’s likely adulterated. 
👉🏼Iodine Test: Add a few drops of iodine solution to paneer. If it turns blue or black, it contains starch and is fake! 

Always buy from trusted sources and stay safe! 

#learnwithadithya #FakePaneer #FoodAdulteration #HealthAlert #FoodSafetyIndia

Are You Damaging Your Liver Without Knowing It?

Here are the Top 3 Worst Foods for Your Liver:

1️⃣ Seed oils (palm, sunflower, soybean)
2️⃣ Alcohol — even one drink harms your liver
3️⃣ 100% Fruit Juices — yes, even the “healthy” ones

Your liver is your body’s detox powerhouse. These foods overload it, inflame it, and set the stage for fatty liver, inflammation, and long-term damage.

👉 Save this for later and share it with someone who needs a liver detox.

#LiverHealth #FattyLiver #learnwithadithya

A dangerous disease is silently rising in India — Non-Alcoholic Fatty Liver Disease (NAFLD).
Even teens and young adults are now being diagnosed due to:
☠️ Junk food
☠️ Sugary drinks
☠️ High-carb diets
☠️ Sedentary life

Your liver stores excess fat from sugar and fried foods — leading to fatty liver, inflammation, cirrhosis, or even cancer.

1 in 3 Indians may already have it. But it’s reversible.

✅ Cut sugar & maida
✅ Eat 1.2–1.5g protein per kg of bodyweight
✅ Move daily
✅ Add fiber + complex carbs

Your liver won’t wait. Start healing today.

This shocking MRI scan shows the difference in muscle mass between a 23-year-old and a 78-year-old man.

The dark area? That’s muscle.
The white area around it? Fat.

As you can clearly see, muscle loss with age is real.
And it starts earlier than most people think.

🔬What Happens As You Age?
After the age of 30, you lose ~1% of muscle mass every year.This rate doubles after you cross 60. It’s called sarcopenia — the age-related loss of muscle.

You might notice this in:
1. Sagging arms
2. Weaker legs
3. Poor posture
4. More body fat around the belly

But it’s more serious than just appearance.

🛡 Why Muscle Matters:
1. It protects your bones and joints
2. Supports posture and balance
3. Boosts your metabolism
4. Regulates blood sugar levels
5. Enhances heart health
6. Strengthens immunity

👉 That’s why older adults often get seriously injured after a simple fall — they lack the muscle cushion to protect themselves.

💪 How to Prevent Muscle Loss:
You don’t need to lift heavy weights or spend hours at the gym.

What works:
1. 30 minutes of resistance training
2. 3–4 times a week
3. Bodyweight exercises, resistance bands, or light dumbbells

Consistency is key — not intensity.
No matter your age, you can build muscle and reverse early muscle loss.
Start now, not later. Because muscle is your real health insurance for aging well.

⚠️ Stop Consuming Dirty Ice Outside – Here’s Why You Must Avoid It

Summer drinks from street vendors may seem refreshing, but the ice in them could be a silent health hazard. 

Most fruit juice shops and sugarcane stalls use ice made from unfiltered, contaminated water. 

The chilling truth? The ice-making process is unregulated, often using dirty water, open trays, reused sacks, and bare hands during handling.

💡 Even if the water is clean, the transport and storage methods are highly unhygienic — exposing the ice to bacteria, viruses, and harmful pathogens.

👉 This can lead to stomach infections, food poisoning, liver damage, and kidney issues — all from what looks like just a harmless ice cube.

✅ Solution:

1. Use filtered water ice at home.
2. When outside, ask the vendor where the ice comes from.
3. If in doubt, skip the ice altogether.

Your temporary relief from the heat should not come at the cost of your long-term health. 

Choose hygiene over habit — because clean drinking practices can protect your gut, immunity, and organs.

#learnwithadithya #streetfood #summerhealth #guthealth #foodsafety

Stop Using Black Plastic – It’s Slowly Poisoning You

Black plastic often contains carbon black, a petroleum-based compound linked to cancer, hormonal imbalances, and fertility issues. It’s also made from recycled e-waste like remotes and electronics—bringing toxic flame retardants directly into your food.

👉🏼 Plastic numbers 1, 3, 6 and 7 must be avoided.
👉🏼 Plastic recycling numbers 2, 4 and 5 are the safest.
👉🏼 But remember: even “safe” plastics can leach chemicals when heated or scratched.
👉🏼 The best choice is to move to stainless steel or glass wherever possible.

🛑 Black plastic containers are the most dangerous – especially when used for hot food. Stop using them today to protect your hormonal health, gut health, and overall wellbeing.

#learnwithadithya #ToxicPlastics #BlackPlastic #uselessplastic

Fix it with clean eating, muscle-building, and daily movement 💪🧠🚶‍♂️

👉 Start today. Your body knows the truth.

Skin tags are NOT moles. And no—they’re not just harmless growths you’re born with.

What are Skin Tags?
They are small, soft, flesh-colored growths that usually appear on:
• Neck
• Armpits
• Eyelids
• Under the breasts
• Groin folds

⚠️ What causes them?
No, it’s not due to sweat, friction, or allergies.
In most cases, skin tags are a sign of insulin resistance — a condition where your body doesn’t respond well to insulin due to:
• Excess sugar & refined carbs
• Processed foods
• Inactivity
• Chronic inflammation

✂️ Thinking of cutting them off?
Don’t. Removing them manually can cause bleeding, infections, or scars, and it doesn’t fix the root cause.

What to do instead?

Focus on healing from within:
• Cut down on sugar
• Eat whole, unprocessed foods
• Move your body daily
• Prioritize quality sleep
• Manage stress

Your skin is speaking to you. Skin tags may be early warning signs of type 2 diabetes or poor metabolic health.

Take action now—because prevention is always better than cure!

#learnwithadithya #skinags  #insulinresistance #diabetes #health
